The governorship candidate of the Peoples Democratic Party, (PDP) in Nasarawa State, David Umbugadu, has said that proper deployment of technologies and synergy among security operatives can checkmate the current spate of kidnapping and banditry in the country.
   
Umbugadu, who stated this in an interview with newsmen in Akwanga, expressed worry over the prevalence of kidnapping and killing of innocent citizens by bandits in the state and the nation at large.
    
He stressed that the state of insecurity is disturbing and must be taken more seriously with proactive actions using the latest technology. 